1
00:00:01,328 --> 00:00:03,828
(synth trill)

2
00:00:14,110 --> 00:00:15,180
- [Narrator] Although fictionalized,

3
00:00:15,180 --> 00:00:18,463
the following dramatization
is inspired by actual events.

4
00:00:19,742 --> 00:00:22,612
(people chattering)

5
00:00:22,612 --> 00:00:25,529
(portentous music)

6
00:00:28,811 --> 00:00:31,498
(dog barks)

7
00:00:31,498 --> 00:00:34,581
(police siren wails)

8
00:00:35,758 --> 00:00:38,258
(baby crying)

9
00:01:03,024 --> 00:01:04,857
- [Neighbor] Let's go.

10
00:01:06,865 --> 00:01:09,113
(car horn peeps)

11
00:01:09,113 --> 00:01:10,873
- Pick it at 8:00 AM.

12
00:01:10,873 --> 00:01:12,390
And I'm gonna give you...

13
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:15,770
Hey man...!

14
00:01:15,770 --> 00:01:17,180
Hey, that's just my kid.

15
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:18,970
She don't know nothing.

16
00:01:18,970 --> 00:01:19,803
Hey...

17
00:01:19,803 --> 00:01:20,716
Hey, come back.

18
00:01:20,716 --> 00:01:21,549
Oh, man!

19
00:01:21,549 --> 00:01:22,780
Come on, don't do thi...

20
00:01:22,780 --> 00:01:24,503
Don't do this to me.

21
00:01:26,371 --> 00:01:30,958
What am I gonna do now?

22
00:01:30,958 --> 00:01:35,958
What am I gonna do now?

23
00:01:36,877 --> 00:01:37,877
Look at you.

24
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,590
Don't you run away from me.

25
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:42,170
You know what you've done.

26
00:01:42,170 --> 00:01:43,640
Get back here, girl.

27
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,940
You're always ruining things.

28
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:46,773
- Ray, please.

29
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:47,700
Ray, please, don't.

30
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:48,733
Stop this hitting!

31
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:49,566
- Get off of me.

32
00:01:49,566 --> 00:01:51,191
You want some of this, huh?

33
00:01:51,191 --> 00:01:52,092
- [Mary] Don't!

34
00:01:52,092 --> 00:01:53,044
- Don't give me force.

35
00:01:53,044 --> 00:01:54,118
You got to face.

36
00:01:54,118 --> 00:01:55,560
Is this what you want?

37
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,550
Hey, girl.

38
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,635
Hey, you know I'm not done with you yet.

39
00:01:58,635 --> 00:02:00,134
Where the hell are you going?

40
00:02:00,134 --> 00:02:01,173
- Ray, please don't.

41
00:02:01,173 --> 00:02:02,006
You're going to kill her.

42
00:02:02,006 --> 00:02:03,544
Don't you go.
- Please don't.

43
00:02:03,544 --> 00:02:04,443
- [Ray] Mary.

44
00:02:04,443 --> 00:02:05,919
- [Mary] Oh no, Ray, please!

45
00:02:05,919 --> 00:02:09,419
(Ray and Mary chattering)

46
00:02:12,489 --> 00:02:14,009
- [Ray] You know I'm right.

47
00:02:14,009 --> 00:02:15,130
- [Mary] Ray, please, don't do this.

48
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:16,300
Please don't do this, Ray.

49
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,199
(Mary screams)

50
00:02:17,199 --> 00:02:20,166
(Ray yells)

51
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:21,525
- Come on, get back in here.

52
00:02:21,525 --> 00:02:22,740
Come on.

53
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:24,240
Come on, I said get back here.

54
00:02:26,210 --> 00:02:27,553
Oh my God!

55
00:02:27,553 --> 00:02:28,419
- Did you see that?

56
00:02:28,419 --> 00:02:29,911
- Yeah!

57
00:02:29,911 --> 00:02:31,204
(dog barks)

58
00:02:31,204 --> 00:02:32,966
- [Bystanders] Call an ambulance!

59
00:02:32,966 --> 00:02:33,842
Is she okay?

60
00:02:33,842 --> 00:02:35,498
I don't know.

61
00:02:35,498 --> 00:02:36,455
Call an ambulance.

62
00:02:36,455 --> 00:02:38,083
Is that a kid, what happened?

63
00:02:38,083 --> 00:02:39,158
I don't know.

64
00:02:39,158 --> 00:02:42,491
(bystanders chattering)

65
00:02:44,147 --> 00:02:47,480
(ambulance siren wails)

66
00:02:48,912 --> 00:02:52,016
(ambulance radio chatters)

67
00:02:52,016 --> 00:02:55,177
(hospital staff chatters)

68
00:02:55,177 --> 00:02:57,385
- [Nurse] You're gonna be
all right, don't worry.

69
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:58,218
- Miss!

70
00:02:58,218 --> 00:03:00,350
- [Nurse] You'll be all right, just relax.

71
00:03:00,350 --> 00:03:01,612
- [Doctor] Check the
vitals, get her cleaned up.

72
00:03:01,612 --> 00:03:02,445
I'm heading down to OR.

73
00:03:02,445 --> 00:03:04,062
I'll be back in about five minutes.

74
00:03:04,062 --> 00:03:05,009
- [Nurse] Fine.

75
00:03:05,009 --> 00:03:07,781
(ambulance radio chatters)

76
00:03:07,781 --> 00:03:09,364
We're almost there.

77
00:03:10,209 --> 00:03:11,450
- [Operator] To Pathology.

78
00:03:11,450 --> 00:03:13,850
Dr. Pullen to Pathology.

79
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:17,839
(hospital staff chatters)

80
00:03:17,839 --> 00:03:18,672
- Hi.

81
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:20,950
You're awake, that's good.

82
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:25,420
I'm Ned Burkett, County Social Services.

83
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:26,253
How you doin'?

84
00:03:28,090 --> 00:03:28,993
Don't be afraid.

85
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:31,048
I'm one of the good guys.

86
00:03:31,048 --> 00:03:33,715
(tray clatters)

87
00:03:36,026 --> 00:03:38,693
(tray clatters)

88
00:03:41,540 --> 00:03:42,393
Can you hear me?

89
00:03:45,594 --> 00:03:46,923
No, I don't think you can.

90
00:03:57,459 --> 00:03:58,890
(office staff chatters)

91
00:03:58,890 --> 00:04:00,602
(phone rings)

92
00:04:00,602 --> 00:04:03,367
- I have 48 open files,
two hearings this week,

93
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:04,960
and I'm finishing up the grant.

94
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,080
I'll get it to you tomorrow.

95
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,820
- Are we up to speed on the hotline?

96
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:11,040
- Almost, but I'm having
trouble with Friday.

97
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:13,600
- We'll staff the hotline first
and then finish the grant.

98
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,433
We have time.

99
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:15,320
- Sorry, I'm late.

100
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:18,180
- You had all those in your desk at home?

101
00:04:18,180 --> 00:04:19,093
- My refrigerator.

102
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,320
- They think you're kidding.

103
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:23,490
Status report.

104
00:04:23,490 --> 00:04:25,990
- I have 56 open files.

105
00:04:25,990 --> 00:04:27,260
I have three hearings this week.

106
00:04:27,260 --> 00:04:29,700
Oh, and I have three families
that need clothes and housing,

107
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:32,480
so if anybody has any
leads, please let me know.

108
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,330
And my carburetor is acting up again.

109
00:04:34,330 --> 00:04:36,530
- And you're way behind in your paperwork.

110
00:04:36,530 --> 00:04:37,900
- I can either service my clients,

111
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,850
or spend all my time writing reports.

112
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:42,200
- Now, there's a compromise
in there somewhere.

113
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:46,380
- Pam, a deaf woman at the
hospital needs your help.

114
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:47,213
- Okay.

115
00:04:47,213 --> 00:04:49,618
- [Barbara] Now, listen, I'm
gonna need those reports.

116
00:04:49,618 --> 00:04:51,701
- [Operator] Dr. Pullen to radiology.

117
00:04:51,701 --> 00:04:52,534
- Ned!

118
00:04:53,412 --> 00:04:54,590
Hi.
- Hi, Pam.

119
00:04:54,590 --> 00:04:55,900
- What are you doing here?

120
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,016
- Waiting for you.

121
00:04:57,016 --> 00:04:57,849
- You're the one who called?

122
00:04:57,849 --> 00:04:59,440
I thought you gave all this up.

123
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,610
- I tried but teaching wasn't for me.

124
00:05:01,610 --> 00:05:02,570
I missed the trenches.

125
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:04,290
- [Pam] Well, I'm glad
you're back, we need you.

126
00:05:04,290 --> 00:05:05,123
- Thanks.

127
00:05:05,123 --> 00:05:06,510
Ah, Laura Keyes.

128
00:05:06,510 --> 00:05:08,650
20, deaf, possibly mute.

129
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:10,110
She was brought in last
night by ambulance,

130
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:12,322
unconscious, no identification.

131
00:05:12,322 --> 00:05:13,340
I'd probably still be trying to ID her,

132
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:16,080
if her father hadn't come
in and demanded a release.

133
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,120
- How badly is she beat?

134
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,100
- Pretty bad.

135
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,690
I didn't want to release
her until I investigated,

136
00:05:19,690 --> 00:05:20,970
and I'm glad I didn't.

137
00:05:20,970 --> 00:05:22,030
Especially after her father,

138
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,230
I'm pretty sure he's the one who did it.

139
00:05:23,230 --> 00:05:24,820
Now, here's the twist.

140
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:25,653
According to neighbors,

141
00:05:25,653 --> 00:05:27,420
she was never let outside the apartment.

142
00:05:27,420 --> 00:05:28,253
- What do you mean never let out?

143
00:05:28,253 --> 00:05:30,760
- They kept her locked up,
even when they went out.

144
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,420
He told one neighbor
that she was retarded.

145
00:05:32,420 --> 00:05:33,350
The only thing that was good for

146
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:35,070
was keeping the place clean.

147
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,410
- How did she end up here?

148
00:05:36,410 --> 00:05:38,630
- She jumped out of a
window to get away from him,

149
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:40,090
down two stories.

150
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:41,700
She's lucky she's only bruised.

151
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:43,910
People next door said the
beatings were a regular thing.

152
00:05:43,910 --> 00:05:45,580
- And they never called the police?

153
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:46,910
- They thought since she
never screamed for help

154
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:47,743
that she was all right.

155
00:05:47,743 --> 00:05:48,740
- Well, maybe she couldn't scream.

156
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:50,210
Did they ever think of that?

157
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:51,320
- Here she is.

158
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,107
Uh, talk to her then.

159
00:05:53,107 --> 00:05:54,791
Make a call, will you?

160
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:55,966
- Thanks.

161
00:05:55,966 --> 00:05:57,292
- Bye, Laura.

162
00:05:57,292 --> 00:05:59,720
- [Operator] Dr. Roddall, please dial 884.

163
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:01,370
- Hi.

164
00:06:01,370 --> 00:06:05,053
My name is Pam Willis.

165
00:06:07,290 --> 00:06:10,410
I'm from the Commission
for Battered Women.

166
00:06:10,410 --> 00:06:11,743
I'm here to help you.

167
00:06:13,568 --> 00:06:14,935
Who did this to you?

168
00:06:14,935 --> 00:06:18,435
(hospital staff chatters)

169
00:06:20,132 --> 00:06:21,333
(Pam sighs)

170
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:24,000
If at first you don't succeed...

171
00:06:26,810 --> 00:06:28,623
Who hurt you?

172
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,900
Do you understand?

173
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,170
You're illiterate.

174
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:48,520
- Late last night.

175
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:50,758
- [Rita] Oh, yes, she's here.

176
00:06:50,758 --> 00:06:51,608
- It's okay.

177
00:06:51,608 --> 00:06:52,672
It's okay.

178
00:06:52,672 --> 00:06:53,947
It's okay.

179
00:06:53,947 --> 00:06:55,188
- Please take a seat.

180
00:06:55,188 --> 00:06:56,557
I'll have the doctor
talk to you as soon as-

181
00:06:56,557 --> 00:06:58,890
- Just tell me where she is.

182
00:07:00,103 --> 00:07:02,310
- That's the man who hurt you?

183
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:03,143
Father?

184
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:05,290
It's okay.

185
00:07:05,290 --> 00:07:07,373
I'm going to talk to him.

186
00:07:09,359 --> 00:07:11,012
He will go away.

187
00:07:11,012 --> 00:07:11,845
Stay here.

188
00:07:15,343 --> 00:07:17,140
- I, I don't care what you say.

189
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:19,310
She's my daughter and I want her now.

190
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:20,584
- Well, I'm sorry, Mr. Keyes-

191
00:07:20,584 --> 00:07:22,870
- Mr. Keyes?

192
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,230
I'm Pam Willis.

193
00:07:24,230 --> 00:07:25,660
If you want information
about your daughter,

194
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:26,640
you're gonna have to talk to me.

195
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,350
She's my client.

196
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:29,183
- [Ray] Client?

197
00:07:29,183 --> 00:07:30,530
What are you talking about?

198
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:32,500
- Your daughter has been badly beaten.

199
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,630
I'm here to make sure that
she receives adequate care,

200
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:37,423
and to help her take steps
so it won't happen again.

201
00:07:38,513 --> 00:07:39,840
- I don't have to talk to you.

202
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:40,673
She's mine.

203
00:07:40,673 --> 00:07:42,330
- She's not yours, Mr. Keyes.

204
00:07:42,330 --> 00:07:43,400
She's of legal age,

205
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,037
and she told me she
doesn't want to see you.

206
00:07:45,037 --> 00:07:46,760
- You're a liar.

207
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:48,050
She didn't tell you anything.

208
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,330
She can't talk.

209
00:07:49,330 --> 00:07:50,803
- I understood her perfectly.

210
00:07:51,890 --> 00:07:53,850
- She's here and I'm gonna find her.

211
00:07:53,850 --> 00:07:55,070
- If you don't leave immediately,

212
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:57,400
I will call security
and have you arrested.

213
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,710
- This is none of your business?

214
00:07:58,710 --> 00:08:00,840
- You assaulted her,
that made it my business.

215
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:03,080
- She's a lying whore.

216
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,890
If you think she's black
and blue now, you just wait.

217
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:07,560
- This case is under investigation.

218
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,290
If you persist in trying to see my client

219
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:11,490
without her consent, you'll
find yourself in jail.

220
00:08:11,490 --> 00:08:12,633
Do you understand?

221
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:19,160
(Pam sighs)

222
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,141
- A real charmer?

223
00:08:20,141 --> 00:08:21,610
- Yeah.

224
00:08:21,610 --> 00:08:22,600
Is her room ready?

225
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,520
- If it isn't, I'll get it ready myself.

226
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,353
- Thanks, Rita.

227
00:08:27,255 --> 00:08:28,463
(sighs) I'll try later.

228
00:08:28,463 --> 00:08:31,110
(phone rings)

229
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,620
- How's it going?

230
00:08:32,620 --> 00:08:34,060
- [Pam] Don't ask.

231
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:36,700
- Purview had two beds an hour ago.

232
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,070
- They don't take deaf clients,

233
00:08:38,070 --> 00:08:39,520
and the few that do are full.

234
00:08:41,370 --> 00:08:42,980
How long have we been doing this?

235
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:45,040
- More years than I care to remember.

236
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:47,850
- Why does it seem to be
getting worse instead of better?

237
00:08:47,850 --> 00:08:48,980
- Well, we're making a difference.

238
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:51,600
I mean, last year alone,
we did a 4% increase-

239
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,610
- Barbara, you're getting
to be as bad as my ex

240
00:08:53,610 --> 00:08:56,050
with those damn baseball statistics.

241
00:08:56,050 --> 00:08:57,700
- I'm sorry, it's pure reflex.

242
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:59,800
Before I hit people up for a donation,

243
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:01,530
I give them the stats.

244
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:03,952
- Don't talk to me, I
don't have any money.

245
00:09:03,952 --> 00:09:05,220
- I know.

246
00:09:05,220 --> 00:09:06,513
I sign your checks.

247
00:09:09,463 --> 00:09:12,304
(woman announces over intercom)

248
00:09:12,304 --> 00:09:13,295
(elevator bell dings)

249
00:09:13,295 --> 00:09:15,404
(people chatter)

250
00:09:15,404 --> 00:09:16,237
- Hi.

251
00:09:16,237 --> 00:09:17,470
- I didn't expect to see you today.

252
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:18,303
- The hospital called me.

253
00:09:18,303 --> 00:09:19,950
The father showed up and
tried to drag her out.

254
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:21,910
Luckily, the security guy stopped him.

255
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:22,860
- Is she okay?

256
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:24,610
- She's scared, but she's okay.

257
00:09:24,610 --> 00:09:26,620
Listen, I'm arranging
for a restraining order.

258
00:09:26,620 --> 00:09:28,784
As soon as you think she's
ready, we'll file charges.

259
00:09:28,784 --> 00:09:30,250
- That could be a while.

260
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,123
She's illiterate.

261
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:32,893
- She doesn't sign?

262
00:09:32,893 --> 00:09:34,760
- She doesn't even know what signing is,

263
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,820
or words, the alphabet.

264
00:09:36,820 --> 00:09:38,020
That animal kept her locked up

265
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:39,720
and didn't teach her anything.

266
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:40,750
- He said she's retarded.

267
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:41,970
- I don't think so.

268
00:09:41,970 --> 00:09:43,850
I want to get her tested,
but I have to figure out

269
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:45,890
how to pay for it first.

270
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,513
- Here.

271
00:09:47,513 --> 00:09:49,210
I want you to call this number.

272
00:09:49,210 --> 00:09:50,610
Ask for Frank.

273
00:09:50,610 --> 00:09:51,460
