00:39:07,010 --> 00:39:08,450
- I was keeping her in line.

841
00:39:08,450 --> 00:39:10,640
- You kept her locked up
like an animal for 14 years,

842
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:11,520
and you beat her.

843
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:12,400
- You weren't there.

844
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:13,599
You don't know what I had to put with.

845
00:39:13,599 --> 00:39:15,510
- I have seen your kind a thousand times.

846
00:39:15,510 --> 00:39:16,820
You are pathetic.

847
00:39:16,820 --> 00:39:19,333
- I want those charges dropped!

848
00:39:21,484 --> 00:39:22,317
- You come near me again,

849
00:39:22,317 --> 00:39:24,353
and I'll file charges against you myself!

850
00:39:35,701 --> 00:39:37,282
(Pam sighs)

851
00:39:37,282 --> 00:39:39,777
- We're not going to try the case.

852
00:39:39,777 --> 00:39:40,660
- What are you talking about?

853
00:39:40,660 --> 00:39:42,650
You saw the pictures, the hospital report.

854
00:39:42,650 --> 00:39:45,280
- We don't anticipate a
good outcome to a trial.

855
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:47,520
- But you have irrefutable evidence!

856
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:48,570
- Well, we know he beat her,

857
00:39:48,570 --> 00:39:49,780
even he doesn't deny that,

858
00:39:49,780 --> 00:39:51,930
but he's going to say he was
only trying to protect her,

859
00:39:51,930 --> 00:39:53,280
and things got out of hand.

860
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:54,113
- Give me a break.

861
00:39:54,113 --> 00:39:55,590
Protect her from what?

862
00:39:55,590 --> 00:39:58,360
- He says she would sneak
out of the house at night,

863
00:39:58,360 --> 00:40:00,050
and she was doing drugs.

864
00:40:00,050 --> 00:40:03,140
- She never once set foot
outside that apartment.

865
00:40:03,140 --> 00:40:05,330
We have neighbors who
will testify to that.

866
00:40:05,330 --> 00:40:06,480
- And what kind of protection is that,

867
00:40:06,480 --> 00:40:07,690
beating her half to death?

868
00:40:07,690 --> 00:40:10,288
- You're not telling me
anything I don't agree with.

869
00:40:10,288 --> 00:40:11,588
- Well, then try the case.

870
00:40:12,700 --> 00:40:13,633
- I'll be blunt.

871
00:40:14,540 --> 00:40:17,334
The problem is is her.

872
00:40:17,334 --> 00:40:19,363
She's not going to be
effective on the stand.

873
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:22,020
- I'll interpret for her.

874
00:40:22,020 --> 00:40:25,050
- She's not literate in
sign, and this pantomime

875
00:40:25,050 --> 00:40:27,730
that you two use isn't exactly scientific.

876
00:40:27,730 --> 00:40:30,420
They'll argue that it's your
interpretation of the case.

877
00:40:30,420 --> 00:40:32,250
- It's the best we can do.

878
00:40:32,250 --> 00:40:34,220
She needs the court's protection.

879
00:40:34,220 --> 00:40:36,770
He's violent, and she doesn't
have anyone to take her part.

880
00:40:36,770 --> 00:40:38,890
He has kept her as an illiterate slave

881
00:40:38,890 --> 00:40:40,330
away from anyone who could help her,

882
00:40:40,330 --> 00:40:42,840
and now you're going to
reward him and punish her

883
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:45,090
because you don't expect a good outcome?

884
00:40:45,090 --> 00:40:46,550
- Is he guilty?

885
00:40:46,550 --> 00:40:47,650
Yes.

886
00:40:47,650 --> 00:40:49,010
Should he be punished?

887
00:40:49,010 --> 00:40:49,843
Yes.

888
00:40:49,843 --> 00:40:52,460
If he's found guilty, will he serve time?

889
00:40:52,460 --> 00:40:53,343
Probably not.

890
00:40:57,370 --> 00:40:58,270
I'm sorry.

891
00:40:58,270 --> 00:40:59,103
- You should be.

892
00:41:04,634 --> 00:41:06,150
Don't tell me you're on her side.

893
00:41:06,150 --> 00:41:07,490
- Wait a minute, we're on the same team,

894
00:41:07,490 --> 00:41:08,590
but I'm entitled to my own opinion.

895
00:41:08,590 --> 00:41:09,470
- You think she's right?

896
00:41:09,470 --> 00:41:10,350
- I'm not saying that.

897
00:41:10,350 --> 00:41:11,997
Well, she has tried a few
more cases then we have.

898
00:41:11,997 --> 00:41:13,530
But that doesn't matter, all I care about

899
00:41:13,530 --> 00:41:14,363
is Laura's welfare.

900
00:41:14,363 --> 00:41:15,620
- Well, what do you
think I'm fighting for?

901
00:41:15,620 --> 00:41:16,800
Chopped liver?

902
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:19,270
It's important that this
battery go on record.

903
00:41:19,270 --> 00:41:21,580
His fear of another arrest
will protect her a lot more

904
00:41:21,580 --> 00:41:23,430
than hiding her away for
the rest of her life.

905
00:41:23,430 --> 00:41:25,070
- I agree, so as soon as
she's able to sign enough,

906
00:41:25,070 --> 00:41:25,903
let's bring her back.

907
00:41:25,903 --> 00:41:27,100
- Well, that could take a long time.

908
00:41:27,100 --> 00:41:28,743
- So, it takes a long time, so what?

909
00:41:28,743 --> 00:41:31,690
- (sighs) It really aggravates
me when you're so reasonable.

910
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:33,500
- That's why make an effective team.

911
00:41:33,500 --> 00:41:35,150
You're passion and my temperance.

912
00:41:36,330 --> 00:41:37,350
I'm running late.

913
00:41:37,350 --> 00:41:38,903
I'll check in with you next week.

914
00:41:42,358 --> 00:41:43,477
(Ned chuckles)

915
00:41:43,477 --> 00:41:46,196
(people chatter)

916
00:41:46,196 --> 00:41:49,180
(Pam sighs)

917
00:41:49,180 --> 00:41:51,513
- We will go to court later,

918
00:41:52,590 --> 00:41:53,423
not now.

919
00:41:57,520 --> 00:42:00,610
Laura goes to school first.

920
00:42:00,610 --> 00:42:03,463
Learns to sign so everyone can understand.

921
00:42:06,350 --> 00:42:09,623
Let's go home and enjoy the weekend.

922
00:42:13,979 --> 00:42:16,562
(dreary music)

923
00:42:19,510 --> 00:42:21,133
What's making you sad?

924
00:42:24,970 --> 00:42:27,300
No, Laura is smart.

925
00:42:27,300 --> 00:42:29,393
She learns very fast.

926
00:42:30,576 --> 00:42:33,243
(Ralph squawks)

927
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:40,460
Hearing and speaking
do not make you smart.

928
00:42:40,460 --> 00:42:42,703
Wanting to learn makes you smart.

929
00:42:45,713 --> 00:42:48,433
Pam has a dream for Laura

930
00:42:49,270 --> 00:42:52,570
to go to school, study hard,

931
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:55,363
get a good job, her own house, car.

932
00:43:00,212 --> 00:43:02,962
Yes, Laura drives a car, her car.

933
00:43:09,837 --> 00:43:12,754
Yes, that would make me very happy.

934
00:43:15,261 --> 00:43:17,928
(bird twitters)

935
00:43:25,010 --> 00:43:27,593
(lively music)

936
00:43:29,708 --> 00:43:30,541
Whoo!

937
00:43:50,419 --> 00:43:51,252
Move.

938
00:43:53,319 --> 00:43:54,152
That's it.

939
00:43:56,594 --> 00:43:58,181
Yeah!

940
00:43:58,181 --> 00:43:59,014
Whoo!

941
00:43:59,928 --> 00:44:00,761
All right.

942
00:44:04,345 --> 00:44:06,928
(gentle music)

943
00:44:23,697 --> 00:44:25,030
Yes, I miss her.

944
00:44:27,649 --> 00:44:29,483
Sarah, don't worry.

945
00:44:30,497 --> 00:44:31,843
Laura's here now.

946
00:44:34,140 --> 00:44:35,997
Laura take care of Pam.

947
00:44:38,516 --> 00:44:39,849
That's so sweet.

948
00:44:44,276 --> 00:44:47,155
(fire alarm blares)

949
00:44:47,155 --> 00:44:49,133
(Pam gasps)

950
00:44:49,133 --> 00:44:51,466
(Pam yells)

951
00:44:52,815 --> 00:44:57,815
Turn it off! (screams)

952
00:44:58,522 --> 00:44:59,446
My ears!

953
00:44:59,446 --> 00:45:00,515
My ears!

954
00:45:00,515 --> 00:45:01,515
Turn it off!

955
00:45:04,370 --> 00:45:06,531
(Pam groans)

956
00:45:06,531 --> 00:45:09,031
(Pam yelling)

957
00:45:15,710 --> 00:45:20,710
This is Pam Willis at 2311 Shady Avenue.

958
00:45:20,870 --> 00:45:23,240
I share my home with a deaf woman.

959
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:26,520
So if you hear this recording,
there is an emergency.

960
00:45:26,520 --> 00:45:28,290
Please come immediately.

961
00:45:28,290 --> 00:45:30,680
This is Pam Willis...

962
00:45:30,680 --> 00:45:33,238
- [Nurse] Right, well, there's
nobody in the lab right now.

963
00:45:33,238 --> 00:45:36,029
(woman announces over intercom)

964
00:45:36,029 --> 00:45:38,532
(people chattering)

965
00:45:38,532 --> 00:45:42,270
(elevator bell dings)

966
00:45:42,270 --> 00:45:43,920
- Excuse me, are you Davidson?

967
00:45:43,920 --> 00:45:45,470
- Yes.

968
00:45:45,470 --> 00:45:47,112
- Your mother's gonna be just fine.

969
00:45:47,112 --> 00:45:50,529
(ambulance siren blares)

970
00:45:54,223 --> 00:45:57,390
(elevator bell dings)

971
00:46:00,702 --> 00:46:01,950
- Um...

972
00:46:01,950 --> 00:46:02,783
Pam

973
00:46:03,940 --> 00:46:05,953
will be all right.

974
00:46:17,259 --> 00:46:20,199
(door handle clicks)

975
00:46:20,199 --> 00:46:23,366
(elevator bell dings)

976
00:46:25,635 --> 00:46:26,552
- I'm okay.

977
00:46:27,530 --> 00:46:28,363
Let's go.

978
00:46:30,967 --> 00:46:31,800
- Hmm?

979
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:33,466
Oh.

980
00:46:33,466 --> 00:46:34,299
Hey.

981
00:46:35,250 --> 00:46:37,634
I got a feeling you look better than me.

982
00:46:37,634 --> 00:46:40,051
(Pam laughs)

983
00:46:41,152 --> 00:46:43,380
(crickets chirrup)

984
00:46:43,380 --> 00:46:44,363
How's the pain?

985
00:46:46,385 --> 00:46:48,210
- Well, I don't feel quite so much

986
00:46:48,210 --> 00:46:51,100
like throwing myself in front of a bus.

987
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:52,100
- I don't know where to put that

988
00:46:52,100 --> 00:46:54,210
on a scale from 1 to 10,

989
00:46:54,210 --> 00:46:55,910
but it sounds like an improvement.

990
00:46:57,669 --> 00:46:58,502
- Thank you.

991
00:46:59,370 --> 00:47:00,203
Where's Laura?

992
00:47:00,203 --> 00:47:01,420
- Cleaning the kitchen.

993
00:47:01,420 --> 00:47:02,550
- I don't want her doing that.

994
00:47:02,550 --> 00:47:04,010
- She wants to.

995
00:47:04,010 --> 00:47:05,130
Let her.

996
00:47:05,130 --> 00:47:06,743
She needs to let off some steam.

997
00:47:09,070 --> 00:47:10,670
She handled herself pretty well.

998
00:47:11,682 --> 00:47:14,130
- She is smart, huh?

999
00:47:14,130 --> 00:47:15,230
- Get some sleep.

1000
00:47:15,230 --> 00:47:16,670
I'll call you tomorrow?

1001
00:47:16,670 --> 00:47:17,503
- Ring softly.

1002
00:47:27,584 --> 00:47:29,194
(dog barks in the distance)

1003
00:47:29,194 --> 00:47:31,944
(birds warbling)

1004
00:47:42,303 --> 00:47:45,092
Why are you sleeping here?

1005
00:47:45,092 --> 00:47:46,175
What's wrong?

1006
00:47:50,750 --> 00:47:52,743
You didn't hurt me.

1007
00:47:54,430 --> 00:47:56,660
You did everything right.

1008
00:47:56,660 --> 00:47:58,023
My ears are bad.

1009
00:48:05,223 --> 00:48:08,180
(soft piano music)

1010
00:48:08,180 --> 00:48:11,063
I was deaf like you for two years.

1011
00:48:14,260 --> 00:48:15,723
Yes, deaf.

1012
00:48:16,870 --> 00:48:20,713
I was married to a man who beat me.

1013
00:48:21,660 --> 00:48:24,293
Once he beat me so badly,

1014
00:48:25,170 --> 00:48:26,733
I became deaf.

1015
00:48:31,280 --> 00:48:32,517
Many years ago.

1016
00:48:38,514 --> 00:48:40,013
I had an operation.

1017
00:48:42,250 --> 00:48:43,437
Um...

1018
00:48:43,437 --> 00:48:44,360
A doctor...

1019
00:48:46,796 --> 00:48:47,629
Uh...

1020
00:48:50,790 --> 00:48:52,540
Fixed my ears,

1021
00:48:52,540 --> 00:48:55,670
but I still have problems

1022
00:48:55,670 --> 00:48:58,053
with loud noises.

1023
00:49:05,540 --> 00:49:09,270
I did nothing to make him beat me,

1024
00:49:09,270 --> 00:49:12,953
just like you did nothing to
make your father beat you.

1025
00:49:17,623 --> 00:49:20,150
It doesn't matter what you did,

1026
00:49:20,150 --> 00:49:21,943
he should not hit you.

1027
00:49:24,190 --> 00:49:26,640
I thought it was my fault

1028
00:49:26,640 --> 00:49:29,763
that he would get so angry, but it wasn't.

1029
00:49:30,600 --> 00:49:32,203
And it wasn't your fault either.

1030
00:49:38,060 --> 00:49:39,810
No, Laura is not bad.

1031
00:49:49,937 --> 00:49:51,595
(cars whoosh by)

1032
00:49:51,595 --> 00:49:52,428
- Hello.

1033
00:49:53,390 --> 00:49:55,410
As principal of the school

1034
00:49:55,410 --> 00:49:58,300
I never dreamed I'd have
to put money in a budget

1035
00:49:58,300 --> 00:50:01,770
for a choir for an all deaf class.

1036
00:50:01,770 --> 00:50:03,000
The next you know

1037
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:04,750
they're gonna want their own band.

1038
00:50:04,750 --> 00:50:07,483
(crowd laughs)

1039
00:50:07,483 --> 00:50:10,430
Here we have Sister Ann and our angels

1040
00:50:11,290 --> 00:50:14,007
singing from their hearts.

1041
00:50:16,895 --> 00:50:19,478
(upbeat music)

1042
00:50:26,802 --> 00:50:29,240
♪ Up on the housetop reindeer pause ♪

1043
00:50:29,240 --> 00:50:31,744
♪ Out jumps good old Santa Claus ♪

1044
00:50:31,744 --> 00:50:34,097
♪ Down through the chimney
with lots of toys ♪

1045
00:50:34,097 --> 00:50:36,488
♪ All for the little
ones' Christmas joys ♪

1046
00:50:36,488 --> 00:50:38,928
♪ Ho ho ho, who wouldn't go ♪

1047
00:50:38,928 --> 00:50:41,332
♪ Ho ho ho, who wouldn't go ♪

1048
00:50:41,332 --> 00:50:43,739
♪ Up on the housetop,
click, click, click ♪

1049
00:50:43,739 --> 00:50:48,739
♪ Down through the chimney
with good Saint Nick ♪

1050
00:51:06,086 --> 00:51:08,836
(crowd applauds)

1051
00:51:11,267 --> 00:51:15,060
- I'll meet you here
tomorrow, nine o'clock.

1052
00:51:16,361 --> 00:51:17,611
You're welcome.

1053
00:51:19,803 --> 00:51:21,300
- Just 'cause you won't look at me,

1054
00:51:21,300 --> 00:51:22,687
doesn't mean I'm not here.

1055
00:51:22,687 --> 00:51:25,150
You couldn't make those
charges stick, could you?

1056
00:51:25,150 --> 00:51:27,210
Guess there was no one
to tell what happened.

1057
00:51:27,210 --> 00:51:29,100
- There is someone to tell what happened,

1058
00:51:29,100 --> 00:51:31,894
and as soon as she can, she will.

1059
00:51:31,894 --> 00:51:33,470
- You never give up, do you?

1060
00:51:33,470 --> 00:51:34,573
- No, I don't.

1061
00:51:35,980 --> 00:51:38,180
- Well, you're gonna lose this one.

1062
00:51:38,180 --> 00:51:40,300
When she finds out there's
no place else to go,

1063
00:51:40,300 --> 00:51:41,617
she'll be back.

1064
00:51:41,617 --> 00:51:44,034
(bell tolls)

1065
00:52:02,296 --> 00:52:04,796
(phone rings)

1066
00:52:07,850 --> 00:52:08,683
- Ms. Willis.

1067
00:52:08,683 --> 00:52:09,880
- Sister Ann.

1068
00:52:09,880 --> 00:52:12,220
I was on my way to see you.

1069
00:52:12,220 --> 00:52:15,500
I can't believe the progress
you're making with Laura.

1070
00:52:15,500 --> 00:52:17,103
She's learning so quickly.

1071
00:52:18,190 --> 00:52:19,850
- I'm afraid I have some bad news.

1072
00:52:19,850 --> 00:52:21,051
The school is closing.

1073
00:52:21,051 --> 00:52:21,884
- What?

1074
00:52:21,884 --> 00:52:23,220
- Diocese funds were cut,

1075
00:52:23,220 --> 00:52:24,810
and they had to make
adjustments accordingly.

1076
00:52:24,810 --> 00:52:26,570
We were just informed this morning.

1077
00:52:26,570 --> 00:52:28,240
I've been trying to
find Laura a placement,

1078
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:30,180
but it's gonna be difficult.

1079
00:52:30,180 --> 00:52:31,440
- When does this happen?

1080
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:32,890
- The end of the month.

1081
00:52:32,890 --> 00:52:34,810
We're asking all of the
students who board here

1082
00:52:34,810 --> 00:52:37,160
convert to day status
by the end of the week.

1083
00:52:37,160 --> 00:52:38,640
- She can't stay here?

1084
00:52:38,640 --> 00:52:40,330
- Not after Saturday, no.

1085
00:52:40,330 --> 00:52:42,660
She's welcome to continue
class for a month.

1086
00:52:42,660 --> 00:52:44,470
- But it's a two-hour commute.

1087
00:52:44,470 --> 00:52:47,170
There's no way I can bring
her here every morning.

1088
00:52:47,170 --> 00:52:48,590
- I wish there was an alternative, Pam.

1089
00:52:48,590 --> 00:52:49,423
I'm sorry.

1090
00:52:50,940 --> 00:52:52,520
- Okay.

1091
00:52:52,520 --> 00:52:55,662
The Langston School, right.

1092
00:52:55,662 --> 00:52:56,495
I'll give it a try.

1093
00:52:56,495 --> 00:52:57,469
Thank you very much.

1094
00:52:57,469 --> 00:52:58,835
(phone rings)

1095
00:52:58,835 --> 00:52:59,960
Oh, thank you.

1096
00:52:59,960 --> 00:53:01,590
(office staff chatters)

1097
00:53:01,590 --> 00:53:03,310
- Textbook catalog.

1098
00:53:03,310 --> 00:53:05,430
Some county bureaucrat jerks me around,

1099
00:53:05,430 --> 00:53:08,003
I tell him off, and I head
down here for chocolate.

1100
00:53:09,110 --> 00:53:10,253
How's Laura doing?

1101
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:12,713
- Fine.

1102
00:53:12,713 --> 00:53:13,546
She's, uh...

1103
00:53:13,546 --> 00:53:15,624
You know, she's got basics down now.

1104
00:53:15,624 --> 00:53:17,300
She just needs to learn how to spell

1105
00:53:17,300 --> 00:53:19,050
like any other seven-year-old.

1106
00:53:19,050 --> 00:53:21,700
- Man, I hope they teach
her to spell better than me.

1107
00:53:22,744 --> 00:53:23,763
That school was a godsend,

1108
00:53:23,763 --> 00:53:25,513
what would we have done without it?

1109
00:53:26,986 --> 00:53:28,236
- I don't know.

1110
00:53:29,140 --> 00:53:29,973
- Well...

1111
00:53:31,500 --> 00:53:32,703
Back to the mines.

1112
00:53:36,489 --> 00:53:37,497
- I don't know what I'm gonna do.

1113
00:53:37,497 --> 00:53:39,000
The school closes tomorrow.

1114
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:40,120
I still haven't found her a place.

1115
00:53:40,120 --> 00:53:42,230
I'm not gonna send her back to Ray.

1116
00:53:42,230 --> 00:53:43,340
- Lunch is on me.

1117
00:53:43,340 --> 00:53:44,173
- Oh, thank you.

1118
00:53:44,173 --> 00:53:45,010
- You're welcome.

1119
00:53:45,010 --> 00:53:47,080
Worst comes to worst, we'll
put her on assistance.

1120
00:53:47,080 --> 00:53:48,960
- Oh great, then she can
move to a welfare hotel.

1121
00:53:48,960 --> 00:53:51,440
Maybe the junkies and hookers
will get her some work.

1122
00:53:51,440 --> 00:53:52,410
- Well, give me an alternative.

1123
00:53:52,410 --> 00:53:55,290
The shelters are either
full or they won't take her.

1124
00:53:55,290 --> 00:53:56,840
- She's not going to one of those hotels,

1125
00:53:56,840 --> 00:53:58,390
that's not gonna happen to her.

1126
00:53:59,665 --> 00:54:00,498
- You know, maybe you should think

1127
00:54:00,498 --> 00:54:02,900
about letting another
advocate take over the case.

1128
00:54:02,900 --> 00:54:04,460
Ned!
- For your sake.

1129
00:54:04,460 --> 00:54:06,073
- Well, none of them can sign.

1130
00:54:07,500 --> 00:54:08,880
Look, I don't want to
talk about this anymore.

1131
00:54:08,880 --> 00:54:10,090
I can't eat when I'm angry.

1132
00:54:10,090 --> 00:54:11,040
- All right, truce.

1133
00:54:12,339 --> 00:54:13,481
We'll figure something out.

1134
00:54:13,481 --> 00:54:16,231
(people chatter)

1135
00:54:18,566 --> 00:54:21,530
- [Pam] I thought you
broke your right finger.

1136
00:54:21,530 --> 00:54:23,539
- This is new, basketball.

1137
00:54:23,539 --> 00:54:26,960
- (gasps) I didn't know
raising boys was so dangerous.

1138
00:54:26,960 --> 00:54:28,560
- I'm surprised I can even walk.

1139
00:54:31,120 --> 00:54:33,680
You know, you should come by
and play with us sometime.

1140
00:54:33,680 --> 00:54:35,833
We're at Sinclair Park
every Saturday morning.

1141
00:54:37,970 --> 00:54:39,973
- That's when I catch up on my paperwork.

1142
00:54:41,159 --> 00:54:43,303
- You can't spend your
whole life working, Pam.

1143
00:54:44,640 --> 00:54:46,550
- My life is my work.

1144
00:54:46,550 --> 00:54:48,050
My clients don't have a lot of options,

1145
00:54:48,050 --> 00:54:49,500
and that means I don't either.

1146
00:54:49,500 --> 00:54:51,150
- You aren't one of your clients,

1147
00:54:52,373 --> 00:54:54,030
but maybe you should be.

1148
00:54:54,030 --> 00:54:56,010
At least you get more of
your attention that way.

1149
00:54:56,010 --> 00:54:58,130
- I appreciate your
interest, Ned, but I'm fine.

1150
00:54:58,130 --> 00:55:00,080
It's not as grim as it sounds.

1151
00:55:00,080 --> 00:55:01,190
- Just admit, you should start taking care

1152
00:55:01,190 --> 00:55:02,340
of yourself more often.

1153
00:55:03,530 --> 00:55:06,010
Promise me you'll think about it.

1154
00:55:06,010 --> 00:55:07,350
- I promise.

1155
00:55:07,350 --> 00:55:09,000
- Good.

1156
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:10,613
- You can be very exasperating.

1157
00:55:11,790 --> 00:55:13,313
- Look who's calling the kettle?

1158
00:55:16,991 --> 00:55:19,741
(birds chirping)

1159
00:55:26,048 --> 00:55:26,881
- Hi.

1160
00:55:26,881 --> 00:55:28,020
- Hi.

1161
00:55:28,020 --> 00:55:29,900
- I'm sorry I didn't call,
but I was coming this way,

1162
00:55:29,900 --> 00:55:31,460
and I thought I'd dropped this off.

1163
00:55:31,460 --> 00:55:33,880
I've had it on my desk for a month.

1164
00:55:33,880 --> 00:55:35,370
It's a house warming present.

1165
00:55:35,370 --> 00:55:36,203
- Oh, I love it.

1166
00:55:36,203 --> 00:55:37,036
Thank you.

1167
00:55:37,999 --> 00:55:40,730
I'm, I'm sorry I haven't
checked in in a while.

1168
00:55:40,730 --> 00:55:41,948
We've just been so busy.

1169
00:55:41,948 --> 00:55:43,350
- You don't have to check in.

1170
00:55:43,350 --> 00:55:45,437
I'm glad things are going well for you.

1171
00:55:49,656 --> 00:55:52,239
(uneasy music)

1172
00:55:53,084 --> 00:55:54,792
- You coming back in?

1173
00:55:54,792 --> 00:55:56,625
- I'll be right there.

1174
00:56:03,667 --> 00:56:04,500
- Oh, Amy.

1175
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:07,007
It's just gonna happen again,

1176
00:56:07,007 --> 00:56:08,803
and this time he might kill you!

1177
00:56:09,956 --> 00:56:10,956
- I'm sorry.

1178
00:56:19,937 --> 00:56:23,173
(cars whoosh by)

1179
00:56:23,173 --> 00:56:26,006
(car horn blasts)

1180
00:56:30,900 --> 00:56:32,890
- I'm sorry you're not happy,

1181
00:56:32,890 --> 00:56:35,203
but we have no choice.

1182
00:56:38,830 --> 00:56:41,783
Your friends will come
and visit you, I promise.

1183
00:56:57,300 --> 00:56:58,930
That's enough!

1184
00:56:58,930 --> 00:57:00,183
We have to leave!

1185
00:57:05,120 --> 00:57:08,380
You know, I could be at home
taking a bath, or reading,

1186
00:57:08,380 --> 00:57:11,510
or lying on a beach somewhere
drinking something pink.

1187
00:57:11,510 --> 00:57:13,790
But, no, I have to give
up any pretense of a life

1188
00:57:13,790 --> 00:57:16,660
to take care of people
who don't have a clue.

1189
00:57:16,660 --> 00:57:18,640
I'm sorry you have to leave your friends,

1190
00:57:18,640 --> 00:57:20,620
but you have to learn about priorities,

1191
00:57:20,620 --> 00:57:22,838
like having a roof over your head.

1192
00:57:22,838 --> 00:57:25,154
And Amy, well, you'll be glad
to know she's alive and well.

1193
00:57:25,154 --> 00:57:27,654
(tense music)

1194
00:57:28,804 --> 00:57:32,756
I might as well just throw
my life down a rafter.

1195
00:57:32,756 --> 00:57:36,064
(Pam chatters quietly)

1196
00:57:36,064 --> 00:57:36,922
What are you doing?

1197
00:57:36,922 --> 00:57:39,412
(brakes screech)

1198
00:57:39,412 --> 00:57:40,245
Wait!

1199
00:57:51,975 --> 00:57:52,808
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

1200
00:57:53,730 --> 00:57:56,613
Not Laura's house, Pam's house.

1201
00:57:59,010 --> 00:58:02,872
Not Laura's house, Pam's house.

1202
00:58:02,872 --> 00:58:04,766
Pam's house.

1203
00:58:04,766 --> 00:58:07,877
No, no, you're never
going back there again.

1204
00:58:07,877 --> 00:58:08,916
Never.

1205
00:58:08,916 --> 00:58:10,408
Never.

1206
00:58:10,408 --> 00:58:11,383
Never.

1207
00:58:11,383 --> 00:58:13,800
(soft music)

1208
00:58:14,894 --> 00:58:15,727
Okay.

1209
00:58:22,756 --> 00:58:26,089
(office staff chatters)

1210
00:58:27,611 --> 00:58:28,920
- Barbara?

1211
00:58:28,920 --> 00:58:29,753
- Hey.

1212
00:58:29,753 --> 00:58:30,860
On the facilities list,

1213
00:58:30,860 --> 00:58:33,010
you forgot the Catholic Mission Home.

1214
00:58:33,010 --> 00:58:34,510
- No, I didn't.

1215
00:58:34,510 --> 00:58:36,340
- It's not here.

1216
00:58:36,340 --> 00:58:38,700
- Well, that's, that's
because it's closed.

1217
00:58:38,700 --> 00:58:41,480
- It's open, Pam has a client there.

1218
00:58:41,480 --> 00:58:42,860
- Had...

1219
00:58:42,860 --> 00:58:44,043
It closed a month ago.

1220
00:58:46,490 --> 00:58:47,620
- You sure?

1221
00:58:47,620 --> 00:58:48,453
- Yeah.

1222
00:58:50,190 --> 00:58:51,023
- Thanks.

1223
00:58:58,039 --> 00:58:59,843
(washing machine hums)

1224
00:58:59,843 --> 00:59:02,343
(door knocks)

1225
00:59:05,080 --> 00:59:07,580
(door knocks)

1226
00:59:11,260 --> 00:59:12,093
- Barbara?

1227
00:59:12,093 --> 00:59:12,926
- Laura's here.

1228
00:59:15,542 --> 00:59:16,375
- Yes.

1229
00:59:16,375 --> 00:59:18,390
- She's been here all month.

1230
00:59:18,390 --> 00:59:19,223
- Yes, but I-

1231
00:59:19,223 --> 00:59:20,370
- No buts.

1232
00:59:20,370 --> 00:59:21,900
You lied to me.

1233
00:59:21,900 --> 00:59:23,070
- I didn't have any choice.

1234
00:59:23,070 --> 00:59:25,320
- I don't know how to
make this any more clear.

1235
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:27,250
You are required by law to act

1236
00:59:27,250 --> 00:59:28,920
in the best interest of your client,

1237
00:59:28,920 --> 00:59:32,140
and bringing her home
isn't in it by a long shot.

1238
00:59:32,140 --> 00:59:32,973
- What do you want me to do?

1239
00:59:32,973 --> 00:59:35,430
- Keeping her here is not an option.

1240
00:59:35,430 --> 00:59:36,440
- What do you want me to do?

1241
00:59:36,440 --> 00:59:38,123
- If I could hand you a list of options-

1242
00:59:38,123 --> 00:59:39,307
- What do you want me to!

1243
00:59:39,307 --> 00:59:41,650
- I want you to do your job!

1244
00:59:41,650 --> 00:59:43,180
Don't you think it kills everyone

1245
00:59:43,180 --> 00:59:46,580
to have to send somebody back
to the hell they came from?

1246
00:59:46,580 --> 00:59:48,550
- I don't know what happened to you.

1247
00:59:48,550 --> 00:59:50,280
When we started, we were
gonna save the world

1248
00:59:50,280 --> 00:59:52,630
if it killed us, and now
here we are 15 years later,

1249
00:59:52,630 --> 00:59:55,550
and you're ordering me to
just throw someone away?

1250
00:59:55,550 --> 00:59:57,750
Is that what authority
does, makes you callous?

1251
00:59:57,750 --> 00:59:58,650
- Are you through?

1252
00:59:59,590 --> 01:00:03,163
- I didn't mean that, but
I, I have to keep her safe.

1253
01:00:05,890 --> 01:00:08,090
- Aren't you mistaking
her for someone else?

1254
01:00:11,220 --> 01:00:12,053
Look.

1255
01:00:13,010 --> 01:00:14,710
You got a week.

1256
01:00:14,710 --> 01:00:17,673
If she's not out of this
house, you're fired.

1257
01:00:24,456 --> 01:00:26,789
(Pam sighs)

1258
01:00:28,221 --> 01:00:31,221
(people chattering)

1259
01:00:33,511 --> 01:00:34,644
- [Ned] Pam.

1260
01:00:34,644 --> 01:00:35,686
- Ned, hi.

1261
01:00:35,686 --> 01:00:37,818
- Hi, I got Laura into the
Pearson Learning Center.

1262
01:00:37,818 --> 01:00:39,610
- I thought that was for people
with physical disabilities.

1263
01:00:39,610 --> 01:00:40,810
- Well, it is primarily.

1264
01:00:40,810 --> 01:00:42,280
They do have some
hearing-impaired residents,

1265
01:00:42,280 --> 01:00:44,002
and the best part is she'll
be in school every day.

1266
01:00:44,002 --> 01:00:45,283
- You're amazing!

1267
01:00:45,283 --> 01:00:46,180
I can't thank you enough.

1268
01:00:46,180 --> 01:00:47,570
- You can try.

1269
01:00:47,570 --> 01:00:48,980
- I got to go.

1270
01:00:48,980 --> 01:00:49,951
You're a lifesaver.

1271
01:00:49,951 --> 01:00:50,784
I'll call you later.

1272
01:00:50,784 --> 01:00:53,284
(alarm beeps)

1273
01:00:57,446 --> 01:00:58,562
- All right, heads up now.

1274
01:00:58,562 --> 01:01:00,385
There you go.

1275
01:01:00,385 --> 01:01:02,454
(man laughs)

1276
01:01:02,454 --> 01:01:03,370
- [Players] Are you kidding me?

1277
01:01:03,370 --> 01:01:04,473
That's got to be a traveling violation.

1278
01:01:04,473 --> 01:01:05,635
Way to go, John.

1279
01:01:05,635 --> 01:01:07,235
Over here, come on, pass it!

1280
01:01:07,235 --> 01:01:08,164
Pass it!

1281
01:01:08,164 --> 01:01:10,018
(players yell)

1282
01:01:10,018 --> 01:01:10,893
Over here!

1283
01:01:10,893 --> 01:01:12,112
Pass it to me, I got it!

1284
01:01:12,112 --> 01:01:13,647
(players groan)

1285
01:01:13,647 --> 01:01:16,647
(radio plays music)

1286
01:01:17,938 --> 01:01:20,998
(residents chatter)

1287
01:01:20,998 --> 01:01:23,790
(whistle shrills)

1288
01:01:23,790 --> 01:01:26,240
- Hi, I'm Pam Willis.

1289
01:01:26,240 --> 01:01:27,690
- John Sanchez.

1290
01:01:27,690 --> 01:01:28,640
This must be Laura.

1291
01:01:31,530 --> 01:01:34,170
- She's not too thrilled about being here.

1292
01:01:34,170 --> 01:01:35,380
- She's gonna love it.

1293
01:01:35,380 --> 01:01:37,120
If you want to just step back here,

1294
01:01:37,120 --> 01:01:39,070
I'll get the forms for you to fill out.

1295
01:01:40,040 --> 01:01:41,210
If you could just fill this out,

1296
01:01:41,210 --> 01:01:42,344
we'll get the ball rolling.

1297
01:01:42,344 --> 01:01:43,600
- Thanks.

1298
01:01:43,600 --> 01:01:45,302
- Have a seat here, please.

1299
01:01:45,302 --> 01:01:46,712
Here's a pen.

1300
01:01:46,712 --> 01:01:48,350
- Thank you.

1301
01:01:48,350 --> 01:01:50,440
- Luckily, we had a space.

1302
01:01:50,440 --> 01:01:52,643
First one in two years.

1303
01:01:52,643 --> 01:01:53,930
- [Pam] Really?

1304
01:01:53,930 --> 01:01:55,520
- I'm sure it's gonna work out.

1305
01:01:55,520 --> 01:01:56,830
But like I told you, the residents here

1306
01:01:56,830 --> 01:01:58,470
are pretty much on their own.

1307
01:01:58,470 --> 01:02:01,020
- Well, she's smart and
she's come a long way

1308
01:02:01,020 --> 01:02:02,720
in a very short time.

1309
01:02:02,720 --> 01:02:04,750
She does need some supervision,

1310
01:02:04,750 --> 01:02:07,060
so maybe your staff could keep an eye out?

1311
01:02:07,060 --> 01:02:08,384
- We'll do the best we can.

1312
01:02:08,384 --> 01:02:09,384
- Thank you.

1313
01:02:11,058 --> 01:02:13,808
(birds warbling)

1314
01:02:14,810 --> 01:02:15,683
See you Friday.

1315
01:02:24,605 --> 01:02:27,272
(forlorn music)

1316
01:02:38,894 --> 01:02:41,560
- Come on.

1317
01:02:41,560 --> 01:02:42,393
Toss it.

1318
01:02:44,193 --> 01:02:45,474
Come on.

1319
01:02:45,474 --> 01:02:48,057
(gentle music)

1320
01:02:53,151 --> 01:02:53,984
Come on.

1321
01:03:03,557 --> 01:03:04,390
- Time.

1322
01:03:09,643 --> 01:03:10,677
Hi.

1323
01:03:10,677 --> 01:03:11,510
You play?

1324
01:03:12,880 --> 01:03:14,327
You play?

1325
01:03:14,327 --> 01:03:15,160
Come on.

1326
01:03:15,160 --> 01:03:16,660
I need one more player.

1327
01:03:16,660 --> 01:03:17,610
They're killing me.

1328
01:03:19,790 --> 01:03:20,623
Please.

1329
01:03:25,780 --> 01:03:26,613
I'm Doug.

1330
01:03:29,501 --> 01:03:30,460
Laura.

1331
01:03:30,460 --> 01:03:31,710
Hey, guys, hey!

1332
01:03:32,659 --> 01:03:33,884
This is Laura.

1333
01:03:33,884 --> 01:03:35,382
She's on my team.

1334
01:03:35,382 --> 01:03:36,215
- Laura.

1335
01:03:37,080 --> 01:03:37,917
Hi, Laura.

1336
01:03:39,161 --> 01:03:40,676
I'm Mike.

1337
01:03:40,676 --> 01:03:41,509
Mike.

1338
01:03:47,704 --> 01:03:49,328
- [Players] Okay, we're up.

1339
01:03:49,328 --> 01:03:50,326
Set five.

1340
01:03:50,326 --> 01:03:51,159
All right.

1341
01:03:53,340 --> 01:03:54,173
All right.

1342
01:03:54,173 --> 01:03:55,006
Oh!

1343
01:03:56,219 --> 01:03:57,052
- Good.

1344
01:03:58,854 --> 01:04:00,104
- Give me five!

1345
01:04:01,140 --> 01:04:04,736
- Okay, all in favor of a comedy club?

1346
01:04:04,736 --> 01:04:06,700
(phone rings)

1347
01:04:06,700 --> 01:04:08,780
All in favor of a picnic?

1348
01:04:08,780 --> 01:04:10,180
- [Employees] Sounds good, picnic.

1349
01:04:10,180 --> 01:04:11,290
- Picnic it is.

1350
01:04:11,290 --> 01:04:12,233
I guess that's it.

1351
01:04:13,880 --> 01:04:15,930
- Hey, Pam, how does
Laura like the new school?

1352
01:04:15,930 --> 01:04:18,460
- I don't know, I haven't
been to see her yet.

1353
01:04:18,460 --> 01:04:19,860
- [Paula] Well, tell her I said hi, okay?

1354
01:04:19,860 --> 01:04:21,052
- I will.

1355
01:04:21,052 --> 01:04:22,519
(phone rings)

1356
01:04:22,519 --> 01:04:25,372
(people chatter)

1357
01:04:25,372 --> 01:04:26,555
(radio plays music)

1358
01:04:26,555 --> 01:04:29,555
(residents chatter)

1359
01:04:35,270 --> 01:04:36,663
- Can you use your voice?

1360
01:04:39,323 --> 01:04:41,233
Can you say Laura?

1361
01:04:45,496 --> 01:04:47,079
Feel the vibration.

1362
01:04:48,717 --> 01:04:50,370
That's my voice.

1363
01:04:50,370 --> 01:04:51,203
Try yours.

1364
01:04:52,729 --> 01:04:54,743
Are you afraid you'll sound weird?

1365
01:04:58,230 --> 01:05:00,767
I became deaf when I was 15.

1366
01:05:00,767 --> 01:05:03,030
So, I know what my voice sounds like.

1367
01:05:04,260 --> 01:05:07,063
I like to talk, even
though I can't hear it.

1368
01:05:08,790 --> 01:05:10,663
I'm afraid if I don't,

1369
01:05:11,720 --> 01:05:13,963
someday I won't be able to.

1370
01:05:16,140 --> 01:05:16,973
- Hey.

1371
01:05:16,973 --> 01:05:17,890
Hi.

1372
01:05:17,890 --> 01:05:18,980
- You remember Mike?

1373
01:05:18,980 --> 01:05:20,707
He came to visit last week.

1374
01:05:20,707 --> 01:05:21,540
What's up?

1375
01:05:21,540 --> 01:05:22,373
- Hi.

1376
01:05:23,210 --> 01:05:24,960
Listen, my plans canceled tonight,

1377
01:05:24,960 --> 01:05:28,040
so I thought maybe you
guys might want to go out,

1378
01:05:28,040 --> 01:05:29,651
play some pool?

1379
01:05:29,651 --> 01:05:30,651
- Want to play pool?

1380
01:05:31,760 --> 01:05:32,593
- [Mike] What's she saying?

1381
01:05:32,593 --> 01:05:33,950
- She doesn't know what pool is.

1382
01:05:35,940 --> 01:05:37,313
- Tell her we'll show her.

1383
01:05:38,248 --> 01:05:39,159
It's fun.

1384
01:05:39,159 --> 01:05:40,510
It's fun.

1385
01:05:40,510 --> 01:05:41,690
- We'll show you.

1386
01:05:41,690 --> 01:05:42,523
It's fun.

1387
01:05:44,153 --> 01:05:46,070
She can't, she has homework.

1388
01:05:46,070 --> 01:05:47,830
- When, when can she make it?

1389
01:05:47,830 --> 01:05:48,663
When?

1390
01:05:51,140 --> 01:05:51,973
- Tomorrow.

1391
01:05:51,973 --> 01:05:53,430
- Great.

1392
01:05:53,430 --> 01:05:55,580
Tomorrow we'll play pool.

1393
01:05:55,580 --> 01:05:56,470
Tomorrow.

1394
01:05:56,470 --> 01:05:58,320
I'll see you tomorrow.

1395
01:05:58,320 --> 01:05:59,153
Okay?

1396
01:06:00,030 --> 01:06:01,183
- We'll go tomorrow.

1397
01:06:05,196 --> 01:06:07,946
(Laura chuckles)

1398
01:06:11,720 --> 01:06:14,637
(soft piano music)

1399
01:06:16,449 --> 01:06:18,190
(Muttso whimpers)

1400
01:06:18,190 --> 01:06:19,790
- Hello, Muttso the Magnificent.

1401
01:06:20,830 --> 01:06:22,353
How are you?

1402
01:06:22,353 --> 01:06:24,436
(Muttso whimpers)

1403
01:06:24,436 --> 01:06:25,936
What's the matter?

1404
01:06:26,907 --> 01:06:28,574
Cat got your tongue?

1405
01:06:31,310 --> 01:06:33,643
(Pam sighs)

1406
01:06:38,435 --> 01:06:41,685
(soft music continues)

1407
01:06:52,144 --> 01:06:52,977
- Laura.

1408
01:06:57,740 --> 01:06:58,573
Laura.

1409
01:07:12,633 --> 01:07:14,913
(stereo plays country music)

1410
01:07:14,913 --> 01:07:17,663
(car horn peeps)

1411
01:07:19,099 --> 01:07:21,599
(Laura claps)

1412
01:07:23,722 --> 01:07:26,899
- If I worked at a pool hall,

1413
01:07:26,899 --> 01:07:29,008
I'd run the table too.

1414
01:07:29,008 --> 01:07:30,656
- Fine.

1415
01:07:30,656 --> 01:07:31,489
- Come on.

1416
01:07:32,375 --> 01:07:33,409
Come on.

1417
01:07:33,409 --> 01:07:36,492
(clients chattering)

1418
01:07:44,730 --> 01:07:45,897
I'll show you.

1419
01:07:53,083 --> 01:07:55,171
(Laura gasps)

1420
01:07:55,171 --> 01:07:56,004
Great.

1421
01:07:56,004 --> 01:07:56,837
Try again.

1422
01:08:00,375 --> 01:08:02,919
(dog barks)

1423
01:08:02,919 --> 01:08:06,427
(children chatter)

1424
01:08:06,427 --> 01:08:09,760
(TV playing rock music)

1425
01:08:13,648 --> 01:08:17,231
- Oh, weekend to the
teenager, my favorite.

1426
01:08:25,805 --> 01:08:29,388
(radio playing rock music)

1427
01:08:42,227 --> 01:08:43,810
What are you doing?

1428
01:08:45,560 --> 01:08:49,720
You left the TV on and
dishes all over the place.

1429
01:08:49,720 --> 01:08:51,783
Are you waiting for me to clean it up?

1430
01:08:54,941 --> 01:08:55,940
When?

1431
01:08:55,940 --> 01:08:58,103
You're supposed to be doing homework.

1432
01:09:00,490 --> 01:09:03,980
If you have time for playing with makeup,

1433
01:09:03,980 --> 01:09:06,440
my makeup, by the way,

1434
01:09:06,440 --> 01:09:08,793
you have time for chores.

1435
01:09:09,846 --> 01:09:11,060
I wa...

1436
01:09:11,060 --> 01:09:13,743
I want you to go in there
and clean up your mess!

1437
01:09:17,400 --> 01:09:18,940
You better straighten up.

1438
01:09:18,940 --> 01:09:21,190
I didn't like this behavior in Sarah,

1439
01:09:21,190 --> 01:09:22,817
and I don't like it in you!

1440
01:09:26,933 --> 01:09:28,554
(Pam sighs)

1441
01:09:28,554 --> 01:09:30,807
(dog barks)

1442
01:09:30,807 --> 01:09:35,057
(children yelling in the distance)

1443
01:09:40,844 --> 01:09:42,177
What am I doing?

1444
01:09:50,328 --> 01:09:53,580
(Ralph squawks)

1445
01:09:53,580 --> 01:09:54,693
Dinner's ready.

1446
01:09:56,327 --> 01:09:58,744
(soft music)

1447
01:10:01,700 --> 01:10:05,400
I'm sorry if I hurt your feelings,

1448
01:10:05,400 --> 01:10:07,993
but I have to work and so do you.

1449
01:10:08,980 --> 01:10:12,843
You have to work very hard to catch up.

1450
01:10:16,712 --> 01:10:19,462
(Ralph squawks)

1451
01:10:23,841 --> 01:10:27,924
Yes, you have to catch up
to all people your age,

1452
01:10:29,220 --> 01:10:30,273
hearing and deaf.

1453
01:10:36,860 --> 01:10:40,100
Well, I'm sick of working
all the time, too,

1454
01:10:40,100 --> 01:10:42,410
but that's what people do.

1455
01:10:42,410 --> 01:10:44,880
They work and they study.

1456
01:10:44,880 --> 01:10:46,583
And if they're lucky,

1457
01:10:46,583 --> 01:10:49,790
they have people they love to go home to.

1458
01:10:51,194 --> 01:10:53,571
(portentous music)

1459
01:10:53,571 --> 01:10:54,404
Ralph!

1460
01:10:56,322 --> 01:10:57,322
Here, Ralph!

1461
01:10:58,847 --> 01:11:00,431
Come, Ralph!

1462
01:11:00,431 --> 01:11:01,987
Here, Ralph!

1463
01:11:01,987 --> 01:11:03,392
(Ralph squawks)

1464
01:11:03,392 --> 01:11:04,225
Ralphie!

1465
01:11:11,276 --> 01:11:12,288
(Ralph swishes)

1466
01:11:12,288 --> 01:11:13,897
(Ralph squawks)

1467
01:11:13,897 --> 01:11:16,647
(birds warbling)

1468
01:11:23,923 --> 01:11:26,756
(van engine hums)

1469
01:11:27,673 --> 01:11:30,673
(people chattering)

1470
01:11:37,220 --> 01:11:38,923
I'm sorry about the weekend,

1471
01:11:39,910 --> 01:11:41,693
and I'm sorry about the bird.

1472
01:11:43,710 --> 01:11:45,273
We'll get a new bird.

1473
01:11:49,070 --> 01:11:51,533
I know you love that bird.

1474
01:11:53,730 --> 01:11:55,833
I know you're not Sarah!

1475
01:11:58,830 --> 01:12:01,130
Fine, you don't want me
to come back, I won't!

1476
01:12:04,942 --> 01:12:07,692
(doubtful music)

1477
01:12:10,831 --> 01:12:13,664
(keyboard clicks)

1478
01:12:15,843 --> 01:12:17,176
- May I come in?

1479
01:12:18,084 --> 01:12:19,153
- You're the boss.

1480
01:12:22,080 --> 01:12:23,810
- [Barbara] How's the stash?

1481
01:12:23,810 --> 01:12:25,124
- Help yourself.

1482
01:12:25,124 --> 01:12:28,457
(office staff chatters)

1483
01:12:30,097 --> 01:12:31,940
(phone rings)

1484
01:12:31,940 --> 01:12:33,053
- Look, Pam.

1485
01:12:34,860 --> 01:12:37,433
I didn't want to see
either of you get hurt.

1486
01:12:38,400 --> 01:12:39,920
There's going to come a time

1487
01:12:39,920 --> 01:12:42,490
when you're not gonna be
able to help her anymore.

1488
01:12:42,490 --> 01:12:44,680
And no matter how close you are,

1489
01:12:44,680 --> 01:12:46,253
someday she's gonna leave.

1490
01:12:47,430 --> 01:12:49,483
You've had enough loss in your life.

1491
01:12:55,040 --> 01:12:56,003
I miss you.

1492
01:12:58,990 --> 01:13:00,690
- I have a lot of work to do here.

1493
01:13:04,500 --> 01:13:05,333
- Cool.

1494
01:13:08,547 --> 01:13:10,046
(dog barks)

1495
01:13:10,046 --> 01:13:12,796
(people chatter)

1496
01:13:13,661 --> 01:13:16,527
(bell tolls)

1497
01:13:16,527 --> 01:13:17,610
- Good catch.

1498
01:13:19,150 --> 01:13:20,350
Gee, hope you're hungry.

1499
01:13:21,840 --> 01:13:24,091
- I could be starving and not
make a dent in that table.

1500
01:13:24,091 --> 01:13:26,720
- Oh, my boys will help
out in that department.

1501
01:13:26,720 --> 01:13:27,820
Is Laura here?

1502
01:13:27,820 --> 01:13:29,227
- No.

1503
01:13:29,227 --> 01:13:30,140
- Is she all right?

1504
01:13:30,140 --> 01:13:30,973
- She's fine.

1505
01:13:30,973 --> 01:13:32,150
She's doing well in her classes.

1506
01:13:32,150 --> 01:13:33,200
She seems to like it.

1507
01:13:34,730 --> 01:13:35,563
- But...

1508
01:13:37,240 --> 01:13:39,200
- She's angry at me.

1509
01:13:39,200 --> 01:13:41,130
- Well, now, that's good.

1510
01:13:41,130 --> 01:13:42,760
She's breaking away from mom.

1511
01:13:42,760 --> 01:13:44,293
I'm going through that times three.

1512
01:13:44,293 --> 01:13:46,170
- [Kathy] Ned, Ned!

1513
01:13:46,170 --> 01:13:48,250
- I think somebody is trying
to get your attention.

1514
01:13:48,250 --> 01:13:49,933
Come on!
- I'll be right there.

1515
01:13:51,300 --> 01:13:53,260
The game is gonna start soon.

1516
01:13:53,260 --> 01:13:54,203
I'm center field.

1517
01:13:57,630 --> 01:13:58,523
Her name's Kathy.

1518
01:14:00,462 --> 01:14:03,246
- I didn't know you were seeing anyone.

1519
01:14:03,246 --> 01:14:04,579
- Just happened.

1520
01:14:05,840 --> 01:14:06,673
I wasn't looking for it.

1521
01:14:06,673 --> 01:14:08,963
I didn't think I was ready.

1522
01:14:10,920 --> 01:14:11,753
It feels right.

1523
01:14:15,330 --> 01:14:17,030
I hope you find someone, too, Pam.

1524
01:14:18,200 --> 01:14:19,190
- Well, give me the name of the store,

1525
01:14:19,190 --> 01:14:20,607
I'll pick someone up on the way home.

1526
01:14:20,607 --> 01:14:23,190
(Ned chuckles)

1527
01:14:24,850 --> 01:14:26,200
- You always make me laugh.

1528
01:14:31,160 --> 01:14:32,170
Hey, you want to play?

1529
01:14:32,170 --> 01:14:33,003
- No, no.

1530
01:14:33,003 --> 01:14:35,767
I'll come by later and watch.

1531
01:14:37,407 --> 01:14:39,157
- Well, don't watch too long, okay?

1532
01:14:42,796 --> 01:14:45,546
(doubtful music)

1533
01:14:46,603 --> 01:14:49,053
(children chatter)

1534
01:14:49,053 --> 01:14:51,970
(birds twittering)

1535
01:15:00,741 --> 01:15:03,074
(dog barks)

1536
01:15:04,916 --> 01:15:07,749
(van whooshes by)

1537
01:15:13,532 --> 01:15:16,532
(residents chatter)

1538
01:15:21,850 --> 01:15:23,070
- Hi.

1539
01:15:23,070 --> 01:15:25,100
Where is, um...

1540
01:15:26,490 --> 01:15:27,330
Doug?

1541
01:15:27,330 --> 01:15:28,540
Doug, where?

1542
01:15:28,540 --> 01:15:30,180
Where is Doug?

1543
01:15:30,180 --> 01:15:31,083
Doug, where?

1544
01:15:35,800 --> 01:15:37,320
Study, studying.

1545
01:15:37,320 --> 01:15:38,950
Studying.

1546
01:15:38,950 --> 01:15:40,850
(Mike laughs)

1547
01:15:40,850 --> 01:15:41,710
Um...

1548
01:15:43,690 --> 01:15:46,290
You, me, play pool.

1549
01:15:46,290 --> 01:15:48,239
You wanna play pool, hmm?

1550
01:15:48,239 --> 01:15:49,389
You and me, I'll drive.

1551
01:15:51,990 --> 01:15:52,823
Great, come on.

1552
01:16:09,813 --> 01:16:13,146
(wistful country music)

1553
01:16:17,498 --> 01:16:21,665
♪ Darling, I'll have you remember ♪

1554
01:16:23,033 --> 01:16:25,249
- Hey, you're aiming too far left.

1555
01:16:25,249 --> 01:16:29,999
♪ Last night's not the way it used to be ♪

1556
01:16:36,074 --> 01:16:39,384
(Sarah chuckles)

1557
01:16:39,384 --> 01:16:40,392
(Sarah laughs)

1558
01:16:40,392 --> 01:16:41,980
- Um...

1559
01:16:41,980 --> 01:16:42,813
You, me,

1560
01:16:44,155 --> 01:16:44,988
one more.

1561
01:16:47,705 --> 01:16:51,433
♪ Been taken for granted ♪

1562
01:16:51,433 --> 01:16:54,841
♪ All good things fade away ♪

1563
01:16:54,841 --> 01:16:59,841
♪ But it's not too late
to learn to start again ♪

1564
01:17:02,096 --> 01:17:03,530
- Sure thing, okay.

1565
01:17:03,530 --> 01:17:07,030
(wistful music continues)

1566
01:17:13,562 --> 01:17:15,979
- I'll see you later tonight.

1567
01:17:17,610 --> 01:17:18,795
(people chatter)

1568
01:17:18,795 --> 01:17:22,795
(truck stereo plays rock music)

1569
01:17:45,712 --> 01:17:48,462
(frogs croaking)

1570
01:17:50,630 --> 01:17:51,463
Oh, home.

1571
01:17:51,463 --> 01:17:52,296
Oh, you want to go home?

1572
01:17:52,296 --> 01:17:55,930
Listen, I'm gonna take you home, okay?

1573
01:17:55,930 --> 01:17:57,704
But I need something first.

1574
01:17:57,704 --> 01:17:59,000
(tense music)

1575
01:17:59,000 --> 01:17:59,833
Okay?

1576
01:18:01,057 --> 01:18:01,890
It's okay.

1577
01:18:02,843 --> 01:18:04,350
It's okay.

1578
01:18:04,350 --> 01:18:05,183
Stop it.

1579
01:18:08,770 --> 01:18:10,060
(Laura squeals)

1580
01:18:10,060 --> 01:18:11,880
Stop it, okay?

1581
01:18:11,880 --> 01:18:13,066
Just give me a kiss.

1582
01:18:13,066 --> 01:18:15,733
(Laura squeals)

1583
01:18:16,913 --> 01:18:19,663
(Laura whimpers)

1584
01:18:21,266 --> 01:18:23,933
(Laura screams)

1585
01:18:29,199 --> 01:18:30,032
Bitch!

1586
01:18:32,673 --> 01:18:35,173
(phone rings)

1587
01:18:41,201 --> 01:18:42,034
- Hello?

1588
01:18:42,034 --> 01:18:43,350
- [John] Is this Pam?

1589
01:18:43,350 --> 01:18:44,600
- Yes.

1590
01:18:44,600 --> 01:18:46,600
- This is John Sanchez at Pearson.

1591
01:18:46,600 --> 01:18:48,190
Is Laura with you?

1592
01:18:48,190 --> 01:18:49,810
- No.

1593
01:18:49,810 --> 01:18:50,653
Isn't she there?

1594
01:18:52,230 --> 01:18:54,000
- We did a bed check, she's missing.

1595
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:55,050
- I'll be right over.

1596
01:18:58,631 --> 01:19:01,464
(van engine hums)

1597
01:19:02,415 --> 01:19:05,425
(crickets chirrup)

1598
01:19:05,425 --> 01:19:06,343
- When was the last
time you talked to her?

1599
01:19:06,343 --> 01:19:08,300
- I can't handle any I
told you so's right now.

1600
01:19:08,300 --> 01:19:09,190
- That's not what I meant.

1601
01:19:09,190 --> 01:19:11,530
I just wonder whether her
father might've found her.

1602
01:19:11,530 --> 01:19:12,480
- I don't think so.

1603
01:19:14,090 --> 01:19:15,403
She's angry at me.

1604
01:19:17,080 --> 01:19:18,100
Maybe I pushed too hard,

1605
01:19:18,100 --> 01:19:19,990
maybe we got too close.

1606
01:19:19,990 --> 01:19:21,260
I just wanted to make it-

1607
01:19:21,260 --> 01:19:22,590
Don't blame yourself.
- Why not?

1608
01:19:22,590 --> 01:19:23,630
You knew this would happen.

1609
01:19:23,630 --> 01:19:24,740
I screwed up.

1610
01:19:24,740 --> 01:19:26,250
- You broke every rule in the book,

1611
01:19:26,250 --> 01:19:28,310
and you're a royal pain in the ass,

1612
01:19:28,310 --> 01:19:30,020
but you're the only one who cared enough

1613
01:19:30,020 --> 01:19:31,978
to make sure she got a chance.

1614
01:19:31,978 --> 01:19:33,470
(Pam sighs)

1615
01:19:33,470 --> 01:19:34,303
- John?

1616
01:19:35,380 --> 01:19:36,213
John?

1617
01:19:37,370 --> 01:19:38,460
Is she back?

1618
01:19:38,460 --> 01:19:39,860
- No.

1619
01:19:39,860 --> 01:19:40,713
- What did the police say?

1620
01:19:40,713 --> 01:19:42,860
- They said call back
in a couple of hours,

1621
01:19:42,860 --> 01:19:44,027
if she's still not back.

1622
01:19:44,027 --> 01:19:45,830
Great.
- You have no idea

1623
01:19:45,830 --> 01:19:46,692
where she went?

1624
01:19:46,692 --> 01:19:47,630
- No.

1625
01:19:47,630 --> 01:19:48,720
- What about her clothes?

1626
01:19:48,720 --> 01:19:50,290
- They're still in her room.

1627
01:19:50,290 --> 01:19:52,320
I have two staff people looking,

1628
01:19:52,320 --> 01:19:53,570
that's all I had to send.

1629
01:19:57,040 --> 01:19:58,580
We're handling it, Doug.

1630
01:19:58,580 --> 01:19:59,790
- I saw her earlier today.

1631
01:19:59,790 --> 01:20:00,623
- When?

1632
01:20:00,623 --> 01:20:02,260
- Around dinnertime.

1633
01:20:02,260 --> 01:20:04,130
She and Mike were heading to his car.

1634
01:20:04,130 --> 01:20:04,963
- Who's Mike?

1635
01:20:04,963 --> 01:20:06,710
- Just a guy.

1636
01:20:06,710 --> 01:20:07,960
He hangs out here sometimes.

1637
01:20:07,960 --> 01:20:09,590
- Laura knows him?

1638
01:20:09,590 --> 01:20:10,870
- A little.

1639
01:20:10,870 --> 01:20:12,540
He took us to play pool.

1640
01:20:12,540 --> 01:20:13,540
It's where he works.

1641
01:20:14,600 --> 01:20:16,573
- Would he hurt her?

1642
01:20:18,855 --> 01:20:20,503
- I don't know.

1643
01:20:20,503 --> 01:20:21,853
I don't know him that well.

1644
01:20:22,710 --> 01:20:23,543
I should've stopped them.

1645
01:20:23,543 --> 01:20:24,720
- Do you know where he lives?

1646
01:20:24,720 --> 01:20:26,270
Where is this pool hall?

1647
01:20:26,270 --> 01:20:28,670
- Fantasia Pool Hall, a
few blocks down Central.

1648
01:20:29,859 --> 01:20:31,901
(suspenseful music)

1649
01:20:31,901 --> 01:20:34,818
(crickets chirrup)

1650
01:20:38,874 --> 01:20:41,457
(door rattles)

1651
01:20:43,384 --> 01:20:44,879
- We're closed.

1652
01:20:44,879 --> 01:20:46,750
- We're from Pearson Learning Center.

1653
01:20:46,750 --> 01:20:48,140
One of the residents is missing.

1654
01:20:48,140 --> 01:20:49,940
- I'm sorry, whoever you're
looking for isn't here.

1655
01:20:49,940 --> 01:20:52,343
- I need the address of someone
who works for you: Mike.

1656
01:20:52,343 --> 01:20:54,010
- What do you want him for?

1657
01:20:54,850 --> 01:20:55,980
- He was with Laura today,

1658
01:20:55,980 --> 01:20:57,480
that's the girl who's missing.

1659
01:21:00,820 --> 01:21:01,653
- Mike.

1660
01:21:02,560 --> 01:21:03,870
- [Pam] Where's Laura?

1661
01:21:03,870 --> 01:21:05,108
- Uh, Laura who?

1662
01:21:05,108 --> 01:21:06,824
- You came to see her today.

1663
01:21:06,824 --> 01:21:08,207
I don't know what you're talk-
- Listen!

1664
01:21:08,207 --> 01:21:10,714
(bottle crashes)

1665
01:21:10,714 --> 01:21:11,547
Oh my God!

1666
01:21:11,547 --> 01:21:12,380
If you hurt her...

1667
01:21:12,380 --> 01:21:14,937
- I, I already said I never even saw her.

1668
01:21:14,937 --> 01:21:17,100
- You wanna play like that,
I'm gonna call the cops.

1669
01:21:17,100 --> 01:21:17,933
Where is your phone?

1670
01:21:17,933 --> 01:21:18,892
- W-Wait!

1671
01:21:18,892 --> 01:21:21,123
- If you know anything,
you better tell us now.

1672
01:21:22,150 --> 01:21:23,023
- Where is she?

1673
01:21:24,730 --> 01:21:25,730
- I didn't hurt her.

1674
01:21:27,240 --> 01:21:28,780
I didn't hurt her.
- Where is she!

1675
01:21:28,780 --> 01:21:29,700
- She's in the park!

1676
01:21:29,700 --> 01:21:30,533
- What park?

1677
01:21:30,533 --> 01:21:31,366
- Creston.

1678
01:21:32,351 --> 01:21:33,923
- Come on, Pam.

1679
01:21:33,923 --> 01:21:35,039
Pam.

1680
01:21:35,039 --> 01:21:35,872
Pam.

1681
01:21:45,691 --> 01:21:47,227
- [Barbara] Okay, there.

1682
01:21:47,227 --> 01:21:48,233
There, there.

1683
01:21:49,730 --> 01:21:50,662
Turn here.

1684
01:21:50,662 --> 01:21:53,495
(van engine hums)

1685
01:21:59,822 --> 01:22:00,905
Look at that.

1686
01:22:03,610 --> 01:22:05,530
- [Pam] I'm gonna stop,
maybe they've seen her.

1687
01:22:05,530 --> 01:22:06,380
- [Barbara] Okay.

1688
01:22:09,110 --> 01:22:10,214
Hey.

1689
01:22:10,214 --> 01:22:12,205
Pam, that's her.

1690
01:22:12,205 --> 01:22:13,320
That's her!

1691
01:22:13,320 --> 01:22:14,433
- Oh, God!

1692
01:22:17,699 --> 01:22:18,739
What happened, what happened?

1693
01:22:18,739 --> 01:22:19,987
What are you doing to her?

1694
01:22:19,987 --> 01:22:21,019
No, I know her!

1695
01:22:21,019 --> 01:22:22,037
I know her!

1696
01:22:22,037 --> 01:22:22,995
I know her, I'm Pam.

1697
01:22:22,995 --> 01:22:25,035
I'm Pam, I know her.

1698
01:22:25,035 --> 01:22:26,265
What happened?

1699
01:22:26,265 --> 01:22:27,721
- She got kind of roughed up.

1700
01:22:27,721 --> 01:22:29,134
She's all right.

1701
01:22:29,134 --> 01:22:30,162
- [Biker] She's okay.

1702
01:22:30,162 --> 01:22:30,995
She's okay.

1703
01:22:30,995 --> 01:22:32,245
- Are you okay?

1704
01:22:34,103 --> 01:22:35,377
I was so scared.

1705
01:22:35,377 --> 01:22:37,794
(soft music)

1706
01:22:44,769 --> 01:22:45,602
Okay.

1707
01:22:47,216 --> 01:22:48,400
Come on.

1708
01:22:48,400 --> 01:22:49,380
Thank you so much.

1709
01:22:49,380 --> 01:22:50,623
- [Biker] Yeah, sure, lady.

1710
01:22:51,830 --> 01:22:52,663
- Thanks, guys.

1711
01:22:52,663 --> 01:22:54,019
- [Biker] Forget it.

1712
01:22:54,019 --> 01:22:55,632
- You okay?

1713
01:22:55,632 --> 01:22:57,032
I was so worried.

1714
01:22:57,032 --> 01:22:59,782
(frogs croaking)

1715
01:23:14,846 --> 01:23:17,763
(crickets chirrup)

1716
01:23:30,639 --> 01:23:33,800
(dog barks in the distance)

1717
01:23:33,800 --> 01:23:35,133
- I was worried.

1718
01:23:36,207 --> 01:23:37,624
I care about you.

1719
01:24:03,750 --> 01:24:05,763
- No, I'm sorry.

1720
01:24:09,600 --> 01:24:12,333
I had my dream for you,

1721
01:24:13,800 --> 01:24:17,507
and I never stopped to ask about yours.

1722
01:24:17,507 --> 01:24:19,924
(soft music)

1723
01:24:25,938 --> 01:24:28,605
Of course, you can have a dream,

1724
01:24:29,620 --> 01:24:32,033
and it doesn't have to
be the same as mine.

1725
01:24:33,920 --> 01:24:35,720
It can be whatever you want.

1726
01:24:41,870 --> 01:24:42,703
College?

1727
01:24:45,509 --> 01:24:46,342
A job.

1728
01:24:53,230 --> 01:24:55,847
Making your own life is a good dream.

1729
01:25:01,607 --> 01:25:02,440
My dream?

1730
01:25:04,335 --> 01:25:06,668
(Pam sighs)

1731
01:25:08,093 --> 01:25:10,343
I have to think about that.

1732
01:25:21,416 --> 01:25:24,416
(people chattering)

1733
01:25:25,896 --> 01:25:30,360
- [Clerk] I think it
should be at 8:30 tomorrow.

1734
01:25:30,360 --> 01:25:31,933
- Don't be afraid.

1735
01:25:31,933 --> 01:25:33,483
Just tell the truth.

1736
01:25:47,060 --> 01:25:50,227
(elevator bell dings)

1737
01:25:52,209 --> 01:25:56,805
(woman announces over intercom)

1738
01:25:56,805 --> 01:25:58,205
Should we go in?

1739
01:25:58,205 --> 01:26:00,788
(gentle music)

1740
01:26:03,094 --> 01:26:04,511
- Thank you, Pam.

1741
01:26:08,816 --> 01:26:11,316
- You've been keeping secrets.

1742
01:26:29,374 --> 01:26:30,707
I love you, too.

1743
01:26:38,384 --> 01:26:41,134
(resolute music)

1744
01:27:28,053 --> 01:27:30,553
(synth trill)

